An All Progressives Congress, APC, presidential aspirant, Bola Tinubu on Monday visited Owo, Ondo State. Tinubu paid a condolence visit to Owo following the massacre at St Francis Catholic Church on Sunday. The APC National Leader joined the Ondo State Governor, Rotimi AkeredoluÂ for an on-the-spot assessment. Recall that worshippers were killed by alleged herdsmen who attacked the Catholic church. Over 50 worshippers were said to have been killed during the attack. 